@startuml
title Deployment Diagram: NeoVex Runtime Infrastructure
' Version: 0.1.0 — update when deployment topology changes
' Reading guide: nodes = machines/environments, artifacts = binaries/files, arrows = network calls

node "Local Machine (NixOS)" <<Developer Workstation — declarative config>> {

  artifact "neovim" as NvimBin <<C binary — managed by nix>>
  artifact "plugin.lua + libplugin.so" as NvimPlug <<Lua + Rust FFI via mlua>>
  artifact "rust_agent_server" as RustExec <<cargo build --release — axum + tokio>>
  artifact "agent_core.wasm" as Wasm <<Optional: wasm-bindgen — portable edge module>>
  artifact "vector_db" as VecDB <<Qdrant / LanceDB — local RAG index>>
  artifact "ollama" as OllamaLocal <<LAST RESORT fallback only — never preferred>>

  note right of RustExec
    Canonical crate stack:
    rig, agentai, ADK-Rust, axum, tokio, mlua
    Listens: localhost:7777
    This is ORCHESTRATION — not inference.
    All inference routes to cloud (Principle 7).
  end note

  note right of OllamaLocal
    Activated ONLY when:
    1. All cloud providers quota-exhausted, OR
    2. Budget cap hit
    UI must show prominent degradation warning.
    Never a default. Never a preference.
  end note

  NvimBin --> NvimPlug : loads at startup via nix home-manager
  NvimPlug --> RustExec : HTTP POST localhost:7777 (primary path)
  RustExec ..> Wasm : optional edge compilation
  RustExec --> VecDB : RAG queries (local fallback embedding)
  RustExec ..> OllamaLocal : inference fallback (last resort)
}

cloud "Google Cloud" <<Primary Inference Provider — Cloud-First>> {
  artifact "Gemini 3 Pro API" as GeminiAPI <<api.generativeai.google.com>>
  artifact "Cloud Embedding API" as EmbedAPI <<text-embedding-3-large or Voyage AI>>
}

cloud "Other Cloud Providers" <<Secondary / Tertiary Fallback>> {
  artifact "Anthropic API (Claude)" as AnthropicAPI <<secondary>>
  artifact "OpenAI API (GPT-4o)" as OpenAIAPI <<tertiary>>
}

node "Antigravity Instance" <<Dev-time Only — NOT runtime>> {
  artifact "Antigravity IDE" as AG <<VS Code fork — research + PR review>>
  note right of AG
    Used by both collaborators for research.
    NOT required at runtime.
    Provides: research env, PR review,
    OAuth token flow for Gemini.
    Decommissioned from runtime path entirely.
  end note
}

database "External Data Sources" <<MCP-connected — external data layer only>> {
  artifact "Git Repos" as Git <<git MCP server>>
  artifact "Filesystem" as FS <<filesystem MCP server>>
  artifact "Web Search" as Web <<web search MCP server>>
  artifact "LSP Bridge" as LSP <<Neovim LSP MCP server>>
}

node "CI/CD Pipeline" <<GitHub Actions>> {
  artifact "PR submitted by AI Specialist" as PR <<proposal only — no merge authority>>
  artifact "Code review by User" as Review <<User is sovereign — Principle 1 + 10>>
  artifact "cargo build --release" as CargoBuild <<Rust compilation>>
  artifact "nix flake check" as NixCheck <<reproducibility verification>>
}

' ─── Primary runtime connections ──────────────────────────────────────────────
RustExec --> GeminiAPI : HTTPS (API key / OAuth) — PRIMARY inference
RustExec --> EmbedAPI : HTTPS — cloud embedding (primary RAG path)
RustExec ..> AnthropicAPI : HTTPS — secondary provider fallback
RustExec ..> OpenAIAPI : HTTPS — tertiary provider fallback

' ─── MCP external data connections ───────────────────────────────────────────
RustExec ..> Git : MCP protocol — data only
RustExec ..> FS : MCP protocol — data only
RustExec ..> Web : MCP protocol — data only
RustExec ..> LSP : MCP protocol — data only

' ─── Dev-time connections ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
AG ..> RustExec : dev-time socket bridge (research/testing only)

' ─── CI/CD flow ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PR --> Review : User reviews Rust code
Review --> CargoBuild : User approves → triggers build
CargoBuild --> NixCheck : verify reproducibility
NixCheck --> RustExec : deploy new binary

note bottom
  Deployment principles:
  - Local machine = low-latency orchestration only (rust_agent_server)
  - Cloud = ALL inference (Gemini primary, others as fallback)
  - MCP servers = external data access only, not inference
  - Ollama = local terminal fallback, never preferred
  - NixOS declarative config = reproducible across machines
  - API keys managed via sops-nix or agenix (never plaintext)
  - WASM artifact = optional portability for edge/browser contexts
  - Collaboration: AI Specialist PRs are proposals, User has sole merge authority
end note

@enduml
